---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Methodology" description="How Pre-Roller Reviews evaluates and scores pre-roll machines.">
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Methodology & Scoring</h1>
      <p class="lead">Our rankings are based on independent research and a weighted scoring rubric. Learn how we evaluate machines.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <main class="container">
    <section class="methodology-section">
      <h2>How Machines Are Evaluated</h2>
      <p>Each machine is scored independently across 7 criteria using official specifications, industry publications, operator accounts, and third-party reviews. We do not conduct hands-on testing.</p>
      <p>No commercial relationships exist with any manufacturer. Scores and rankings are earned through data, not influenced by sponsorship or marketing relationships.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="methodology-section">
      <h2>Scoring Rubric</h2>
      <p>Each criterion is scored 0–10, then weighted to produce an overall score:</p>

      <table class="rubric-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Criterion</th>
            <th>Weight</th>
            <th>What We Measure</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Consistency & Accuracy</td>
            <td>25%</td>
            <td>Weight variance, density uniformity, burn quality, canoeing resistance</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Throughput</td>
            <td>20%</td>
            <td>J*ints per hour at rated capacity</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Total Cost of Ownership</td>
            <td>20%</td>
            <td>Upfront cost + maintenance + material costs over 3 years</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Format Flexibility</td>
            <td>10%</td>
            <td>Support for cones, straight rolls, blunts, infused formats</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Ease of Operation</td>
            <td>10%</td>
            <td>Setup time, training required, day-to-day operation difficulty</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Uptime & Maintenance</td>
            <td>10%</td>
            <td>Cleaning time, parts availability, reliability reports</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Support & Warranty</td>
            <td>5%</td>
            <td>Manufacturer responsiveness, warranty terms, support availability</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Why This Weighting?</h3>
      <p>Consistency and accuracy carry the highest weight because they directly impact brand reputation and customer experience. A machine that produces inconsistent j*ints damages margins through returns and complaints, even if it's cheaper upfront.</p>
      <p>Throughput and TCO are equally weighted because different operators prioritize differently: high-volume operations care about per-unit cost; premium brands care about quality. Both matter.</p>
      <p>Support is weighted lower because it's easier to evaluate and communicate, but still important for operations with limited technical staff.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="methodology-section">
      <h2>Data Sources</h2>
      <p>We use a triangulated approach:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Manufacturer specifications:</strong> Official datasheets and product pages.</li>
        <li><strong>Industry publications:</strong> MJBizDaily, mg Magazine, Cannabis & Tech Today for third-party coverage.</li>
        <li><strong>Community forums:</strong> Future4200, Reddit, THCFarmer for operator experiences and pain points.</li>
        <li><strong>Operator accounts:</strong> Direct reports from dispensary owners and production managers.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>When sources conflict, we flag it. When claims can't be independently verified, we note that in the review.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="methodology-section">
      <h2>Category Badges</h2>
      <p>Machines also receive category badges based on their distinct strengths, independent of overall ranking:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Best for High Volume:</strong> Highest throughput per dollar</li>
        <li><strong>Best for Quality/Consistency:</strong> Lowest variance in j*int quality</li>
        <li><strong>Best Value:</strong> Best price-to-feature ratio</li>
        <li><strong>Most Format-Flexible:</strong> Widest range of supported formats</li>
        <li><strong>Best Entry-Level:</strong> Lowest barrier to automation</li>
        <li><strong>Best for Craft/Premium Brands:</strong> Highest quality output</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="methodology-section">
      <h2>Disclosure & Conflicts of Interest</h2>
      <p><strong>Commercial relationships:</strong> Pre-Roller Reviews has no commercial relationships with any manufacturer. We are not paid for reviews, sponsored content, or product placement. Rankings are not influenced by advertising or affiliate relationships.</p>
      <p><strong>Operator feedback:</strong> When we cite operator accounts, we source from public forums and published interviews, not paid testimonials.</p>
      <p><strong>Updates:</strong> We review and update rankings monthly as new machines launch, prices change, or new operator data emerges.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="methodology-section">
      <h2>Limitations</h2>
      <p>This guide does not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Conduct hands-on testing or lab analysis</li>
        <li>Recommend specific machines for specific operations (too many variables)</li>
        <li>Cover illegal markets or unlicensed operations</li>
        <li>Review consumer pre-roll devices or hand-rolling aids</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We evaluate commercial-grade machines sold into licensed or regulated markets only.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="methodology-section">
      <h2>Last Updated</h2>
      <p><strong>May 2026.</strong> Rankings are updated monthly. Subscribe to our updates to stay current as new machines launch and scores change.</p>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: #0f172a;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 3.5rem 0 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.03rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #94a3b8;
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .methodology-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .methodology-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .methodology-section h3 {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .methodology-section ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .methodology-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #374151;
  }

  .rubric-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
